Trying to figure out what are things I can actually do.... There's so much, it's hard to know where to focus.

@A Scared Doctor and Medical Researcher, scary times indeed.

I'm currently grateful that my daughter elected NOT to pursue a proffered post-doc at the NIH. She isn't going into academia, so she's in an internship in Switzerland (where she earned her PhD in medical neuroscience), which she hopes will lead to a job on the clinical side of things. She was welcomed at the NIH for a brief lab stint to learn some research techniques that she took back to her Swiss lab.

I share your concern for our current situation, which will surely get worse before it gets better.

